    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-04-12T03:29:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-04-12T03:29:00-05:00" n="86"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d86">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">795.00/4–352: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Commander in Chief United Nations Command (<persName
                            corresp="#p_RGMB1" type="from">Ridgway</persName>) to the Assistant
                        Chief of Staff <gloss target="#t_G31">G–3</gloss>, Department of the Army
                            (<persName type="to">Jenkins</persName>)</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d86fn1">A marginal notation on the source text indicated
                        that this telegram was seen by the Secretary of State.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret<lb/>operational immediate</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-04-12T17:29:00+09:00"
                            >April 12, 1952—5:29 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>C 66832. Re opn <gloss target="#t_SCATTER1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Scatter</hi>
                    </gloss>.</p>
                <p>1. The cumulative results of the screening operation as of 2400, 11 Apr 52 are:
                    Read in 3 cols, col 1 total screened, col 2 total to return to Communist
                    control, col 3 total indicating they would forcibly resist repatriation. <pb
                        facs="0178" n="144" xml:id="pg_144"/>
                    <table cols="4" rows="5">
                        <row>
                            <cell/>
                            <cell role="num">1</cell>
                            <cell role="num">2</cell>
                            <cell role="num">3</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>North Korean <gloss target="#t_POWs1">POWs</gloss>
                            </cell>
                            <cell role="num">51491</cell>
                            <cell role="num">21102</cell>
                            <cell role="num">30389</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>Chinese <gloss target="#t_POWs1">POWs</gloss>
                            </cell>
                            <cell role="num">17593</cell>
                            <cell role="num">3467</cell>
                            <cell role="num">14126</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>South Korean <gloss target="#t_POWs1">POWs</gloss>
                            </cell>
                            <cell role="num">14616</cell>
                            <cell role="num">3559</cell>
                            <cell role="num">11057</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>Civilian Internees</cell>
                            <cell role="num">21303</cell>
                            <cell role="num">2628</cell>
                            <cell role="num">18675</cell>
                        </row>
                    </table>
                </p>
                <p>2. As a result of the screening completed in opn <gloss target="#t_SCATTER1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Scatter</hi>
                    </gloss> to date approximately 44,000 North Koreans, South Koreans and <gloss
                        target="#t_CIs1">CIs</gloss> have either refused screening or are in
                    compounds where prisoners representatives object to their compounds being
                    subjected to screening. In addition, some 12,000 <gloss target="#t_POWs1"
                        >POWs</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_CIs1">CIs</gloss> in the hospital area
                    in camp nr 10, Pusan, have not been screened.</p>
                <p>3. To determine a reliable round number and accurate rosters for submission to
                    the Communists, a plan for screening or otherwise designating those <gloss
                        target="#t_POWs1">POWs</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_CIs1">CIs</gloss>
                    mentioned in para 2 above is being developed.</p>
            </div>
